ShortDescription:
Furnished Rooms For a single person or groups.  walking distance to Cornell  University.
Corner of Eddy St. & Buffalo St. 
- Aug., 2025
LongDescription:
Furnished Rooms For a single person or groups. 
Corner of Eddy and Buffalo Street. 
A well maintained large house. 
Walking distance to Cornell University. 

Rent: $715/mo or $795/mo depending on room size.

All utilities and garbage disposal included. 
5 baths, 1 big kitchen. 
Cleaning service provided for common areas. 
Laundry on premises.

Available 8/10/2024, 12 months lease. 

Pls TEXT: Sharon 929 538 9073 (cell); 
www.gooderealtyco.com to view floor plan

ShortDescription: SPACIOUS, SUNNY One Bedroom & a Study in the Heart of Downtown! Rent $1,320.00. Has internet, cable ready, has shower & full tub, close to shopping, fine dinning and entertainment.
LongDescription:
One Bedroom & a Study

- Furnished, cozy, sunny apartment downtown. 

- Plenty of windows throughout. 

- Close to the Ithaca Commons. 

-  4 mins walk to the bus stop to Cornell & Inter-city buses to NY. 

- High-speed internet

- Gas included (for heating, cooking & hot water).  

- Tenant pays for electric - cost depends on tenant's usage.

- Cable ready.
   
- Shower & full tub.

- Short walk to Wegmans for your grocery shopping. 

- A quiet apartment in a convenient location downtown.

ShortDescription: Recently renovated( see pictures) pet friendly,large 350 square foot studio apartment,with full kitchen and bath, 6 minutes to vet school.
LongDescription: Many veterinarian and grad students live here in this small quiet complex of 24 units. All have walk out access to a spacious 2.5 acre grounds located across the road from Fall creek. Trash, parking, water and sewer, professional  and courteous maintenance provided by the owner of 22 years, included in the rent on this updated studio apartment . Laundry on site , and bus service available. Rent w/o pets $820.00 mo, $845.00 with pets.

ShortDescription: Renovated House available near Campus AUG 2025
LongDescription:
House available starting 8/8/2025 - 7/31/2026. 10 min walk to campus. Bus stop around corner. No smoking or pets. Accepting applications for groups of 6.

Includes:
- Furnished rooms with bed, dresser, desk
- Furnished living room and study room
- 2 renovated bathrooms 
- New kitchen appliances
- Free laundry in basement

Internet & utilities not included. Video tour available. Email for questions. More details: www.ferrisplacerentals.com

ShortDescription:
GEM OF A PLACE    NEAR THE VET SCHOOL
AVAILABLE MAY 1, 2025 
2 BDRM
LongDescription: The bottom part of a house with a separate entrance- light and bright and not at all basement-y. Newer kitchen and plenty of room. In a quiet, beautiful country setting near the state forest. Is well maintained and has a propane stove to keep you cozy in the winter, new washer and dryer and flooring. The apartment is centrally located: the Commons is nine miles; Dryden/TC3 is approximately six miles and Cornell is eight miles. Come make it your home. Non-smoking/vaping and pets upon approval.

ShortDescription: A large nice room is available now for Spring + Summer. This is a bay window corner room right next to the Cornell business school. It's in the heart of Collegetown, one block from campus & shops.
LongDescription:
This room has a 4 tall windows including a bay window seat. It's a large room comprising of 175 square ft with a closet. It has an oak desk, chair, dresser, table and a full double bed. The room is on the first floor. It is full of sunlight and charm. This is a traditional student house within a 2-3 min walk to Cornell. It attracts serious scholars who want their quiet, private space.  We provide free trash collection, & Turbo Internet along with premium cable TV.

ShortDescription: Lovely  1 BR plus study apartment in home; 5-7 minute walk  to Collegetown, Law School on Main Campus in family neighborhood. Perfect fo serious law student who hopes to make Law Journal!
LongDescription: Charming apt. i  5-7 minute walk to Cornell Law School in quiet Bryant Park/Belle Sherman neighborhood close to campus. Large eat in kitchen, full bath w/shower, spacious front room and second smaller bonus room, Perfect for law student. The house has an almost perfect track record for its tenants earning places on the Law Journal. If you want to succeed in your studies, live in a nice environment with landlord whom you know and trust to repair any problems as they arise, 224 Bryant is for you.

ShortDescription: Clean, easy living with this 1bd. partial basement apartment available for rent in the Northeast neighborhood of Ithaca.
LongDescription: $1550/mo. includes all utilities (unlimited continuous hot water & heat) except internet and garbage tags. Quiet family of three lives above. Pets and sharing of entire yard are all negotiable. I am open to any requests and always handle a repair quickly. Friendly neighborhood close to hiking trails, Sapsucker Woods, Triphammer Marketplace, and a 5-8min drive to Cornell. Flexible start date with a signed 1 yr. lease.

ShortDescription:
2025 SUMMER SUBLET - Ithaca Commons Private Room
Private a 3-bed-2-bath apartment. The monthly rent includes all utilities besides electricity. Indoor washer&dryer, furniture provided. Female only.
LongDescription: I am subletting this spacious, fully furnished apartment starting Summer 2025, and it’s perfectly situated in the heart of Downtown Ithaca at the Commons. You’ll be just a short walk from the best bars, cafes, and restaurants, with a bus stop conveniently across the street. Enjoy the convenience of in-door laundry and available parking. It also offers great amenities like 24/7 maintenance, internet, a secure entrance, and a rooftop terrace. If you're interested, reach out to st678@cornell.edu

ShortDescription: Motivated sublet! Entire apartment in The Ithacan. 1 bed, 1 bath + office, furnished. Stainless steel, W/D, walk-in closet. Rooftop terrace, gym, business lounge. Available to June 2025.
LongDescription:
Avoid a 12-month lease and save on summer rent! Take over my furnished 1BR/1BA Ithacan Residences sublet until June 2025. Rent will range from $2000-2900/month depending on lease start date. Enjoy in-unit washer/dryer, stainless steel appliances, walk-in closet, and a flexible office space. Building boasts rooftop terrace, gym, business lounge, and more.
In-unit laundry. The apartment is located on the 8th floor, ensuring ample natural light as it's positioned above the adjacent parking garage.

ShortDescription: Bedroom for rent, just 5 minutes from Cornell. Includes utilities and internet, with a small electricity charge. Furnished, shared kitchen and living room with students. Pets allowed with deposit.
LongDescription: A cozy private bedroom for rent, available right away! It’s just a quick 5-minute drive to Cornell and conveniently located near the bus stop. Rent included utilities, internet, and trash collection—just a small electricity charge applies. Pets are warmly welcomed with a deposit! Features furnished bedrooms, a spacious kitchen, a large living room, and a lovely backyard. You’ll share the space with fellow students, creating a friendly atmosphere. Plus, free street parking is available!

ShortDescription: Spring 2025 Sublet – 216 Delaware Ave, Ithaca, NY
LongDescription:
Hey everyone! I’m looking for a female subletter for my room in a spacious 4-bedroom, 2-bathroom apartment super close to campus. (NO HILLS) The room is fully furnished, and you’ll have awesome, friendly roommates!
Rent is $1,170 per month (utilities not included), however I’ll discount it to $600 a month. Move-in is flexible between January 10-20, so you can get settled before classes start. Feel free to message me if you’re interested or have a question! You can move in anytime after 1/10.

ShortDescription:
Peaceful Woodland Cottage in Ellis Hollow for rent! 
Ideal for 1 to 2 people. Property shared with Nonprofit Wildlife Rehabilitation Farm & Farm Sanctuary. 4 miles from Cornell Campus.
LongDescription:
Includes: In-unit stackable washer/dryer, A/C, High Speed Internet Access, jacuzzi bathtub and shower, well water with APEC drinking water filtration system, stovetop, oven, loft-style queen size bed frame, pull-out couch full bed size, hardwood floor, private walkway, 1 covered parking space (1 extra available $50/month), electric heat and propane fireplace heat, back-up generator for power outages, driveway snow removal. 
*Comfort being in proximity to animals recommended. 
*Smoke Free*

ShortDescription: Furnished and spacious, 2200 sq. ft. 6 Bedroom, 2 Bath home near everything.
LongDescription: Fully furnished, spacious, 2200 sq. ft. 6-Bedroom, 2-Bathroom Apartment near everything. - Private Balcony
- Street Parking or Paid Lot Parking

Contact me for more information!

Landlord/Owneris a NYSE-licensed Broker.

ShortDescription: Peaceful, cozy space in a 2 bedroom apartment
LongDescription:
Cozy, furnished room in a quiet, 2 bedroom apartment in Fall Creek. Perfect for visiting scholars, young professionals, or anyone seeking a calm environment.
You’ll be sharing the apartment with a young professional in an atmosphere that is quiet and conducive to work or study. Tennant has one well behaved cat. No additional pets. The apartment includes access to a shared kitchen, dining and living room. Available for 6 months with possibility of extending. Room furnished with bed, table and tv.

ShortDescription: Fully furnished 3BR/1BA apartment at Sapsucker Woods/Lab of Ornithology - $2,100/mo including wifi and utilities for up to three occupants. Includes washer/dryer, dishwasher, large TV, & home office.
LongDescription: This is a fully furnished 3BR/1BA apartment with a home office, washer/dryer, dishwasher, free parking, and immediate access to the beautiful trails in Sapsucker Woods. All occupants will need to submit an application for consideration, must provide a security deposit, and complete an agreement with the current tenant.

ShortDescription: Room available for sublet until May 18, 2025 in furnished Ithaca home, walking distance from Cornell's campus and Ithaca Commons. Renovated kitchen with stainless appliances, heat, A/C, and laundry.
LongDescription:
Sublet is for one beautifully furnished, light-filled bedroom and shared common space, including kitchen, living room, family room, dining room, and sunroom. Tall ceilings, classic Victorian details, formal entry, & Lodge-style sunroom. Distant views of West Hill from all three stories.

Wooden fencing encloses the backyard with stone patio and kitchen garden.

Email current Cornell graduate student at jab865@Cornell.edu.

Subject to landlord approval. Friendly dog on premises some of the time.

ShortDescription: Room available from March to May, just a 5-7 minute walk to Collegetown and Cornell via Hoy Road. Great location for students. The room shares a kitchen and bathroom with three housemates.
LongDescription:
Looking for someone to take over my lease from March to May. This cozy room is in an ideal location, just a 5-7 minute walk to Collegetown and conveniently close to Cornell University via Hoy Road—perfect for students or anyone visiting the university.

The room is on a shared floor with three other housemates. It features:

Three large windows overlooking the side yard with morning sunlight.
A shared kitchen and bathroom.
This is a great opportunity for anyone looking for temporary housing.

221 Tareyton Single family home in quiet neighborhood. ICSD school district. Close to Cornell University. On a bus line. Adjacent to Sapsucker Woods. Tareyton Park at end of street.

ShortDescription: 1 Bed in a 3x3 Bed TownHouse with Garage in Maplewood. All included. Available June and July.
LongDescription: I am looking for someone to transfer my Maplewood lease to for the summer. I currently live in a 3bedx3bath Townhouse (you get your own bathroom). Covers all utilities (including wifi) with in-unit washer/dryer. Parking is available for $135/month. The lease transfer would be effective 6/1 - 7/31 2025. You would have 2 female roommates during this time. One of my roommates has a male cat. 20 min walk (5 min drive) from campus. Fitness center, maintenance, and package room included.

ShortDescription: Summer 2025! Subleasing large studio apartment at The Villager (Cayuga Heights)
LongDescription:
Seeking an organized and responsible graduate or undergraduate student, or a young professional (Cornell-affiliated, per management's request), to sublease a spacious, fully furnished studio for the summer. 
The studio is well-equipped with a bed, sofa, dining table, and chairs, ensuring a comfortable living space. Building amenities include on-site parking and access to a coin-operated washer and dryer. No pets allowed. 
Deposit: $800

LongDescription: 2 story apartment in a duplex with 3bed+1bath. Downstairs includes open concept living room, dining room + kitchen with a built in island. ShortDescription: 2 beds available in furnished 3 bedr apt! PRICE FLEXIBLE!
LongDescription: Two bedrooms are available for sublet in a gorgeous and spacious 3 bedroom apartment, other roomie is a girl/undergrad. Hardwood floors through entire two-story house, large open floor plan downstairs with living room, kitchen, mudroom and half bath. Upstairs are three large bedrooms and one bathroom. Available for a summer sublet, price is negotiable. Possibility for parking space next the house as well. Can sublet one or two bedroom! Watch video tour here of Apt 1: https://tinyurl.com/5xcedah8

ShortDescription: Quiet, Well-Maintained Condo near Cornell – Ideal for Research & Writing
LongDescription: The 850 sq. ft., two-story condo offers a well-balanced mix of privacy and proximity—a quiet, well-maintained home in a cooperative community that includes both longtime Ithaca residents and Cornell faculty, researchers, and graduate students. It’s an environment suited for uninterrupted work, but close enough to campus when needed. The apartment itself is in excellent condition and can be rented furnished (preferred) or unfurnished. Rent is negotiable for leases longer than one academic year.

ShortDescription: Llenroc Mansion Student Housing (Cornell West Campus)
LongDescription:
Llenroc Welcomes Cornell students for 2025-2026

Llenroc (Cornell spelled backwards) is Ezra Cornell’s historic mansion located at 100 Cornell Avenue, just minutes from Cornell University's West Campus.

The mansion has historically been the home of the Delta Phi fraternity, but it is now open for leasing to Cornell University students for the 2025-2026 academic year.

Single room rates start at $14236 for a 9 month academic year lease. Double and triple occupancy rates are available.

Looking for two people to sublet this cute apartment in Collegetown. Lots of natural light and a private porch!

$1000 per room per month plus electric and wifi. $50 off if you water our plants!

Comes with a parking spot in a lot.

ShortDescription: 1 BR in a 2BR Apt
LongDescription:
317 Eddy Street- Van Etten Apartments
- 1 room available in a 2 bedroom apartment
- Off street parking 
- Laundry available next door between Souvlaki House and Asian Grocery Store
- In Collegetown, less than a 10 minute walk from campus
- The Landlord will pay for water and sewer service, heat, gas and snow and ice removal in front of the building.
- Fully furnished living room and bedroom
- A/C unit
- Kitchen includes refrigerator, stove, sink and microwave
- Dates can be negotiated

ShortDescription: 5 Bed 1.5 bath, Student House ALL utilities and parking for 5+ included
LongDescription: 809 South Aurora is a 5 bedroom, one and a half bath house.  This property includes a washer and dryer, dishwasher, garbage, parking for 5+ vehicles and snow removal.  All utilities (heat, water, electric) are included and trash facilities are available. The internet is the responsibility of the tenants.  This is a single family house with no shared spaces or parking. 809 is about a 5 minute walk to IC, 10 minute walk downtown, 10 minute car ride to Cornell and located on a main bus line.

ShortDescription: 1 br on north campus available ASAP! Flexible lease takeover
LongDescription: Looking for someone to takeover a 1 br lease at Brooklane apartments. My current lease is through mid July, but leasing is happy to work with a new tenant on a lease starting ASAP and continuing as long as you need it for. It is a SUPER convenient location on the corner of 3 TCAT stops, a 7 minute walk to campus, and a very short walk to the C2C north campus pickup spot. In-building laundry facility and recently renovated wood floors in-unit. Semi-furnished or unfurnished depending on your needs

ShortDescription: Beautiful recently renovated rental in a country setting, only 4 miles to Cornell
LongDescription:
Clean updated rental with lots of character, just a few miles from Cornell and downtown.  Excellent open floor layout, land, and amenities for memorable gatherings.  5 acre property is surrounded by woods and nature.

Kitchen has dishwasher, gas range, granite countertops.  All spaces freshly painted, new carpets in bedrooms, very clean.  Mudroom and sunroom.  Shared laundry room.  

Large workshop space with an interesting history attached to house, can potentially be worked into rental
